S"{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox congressman\n| name        =Cresent Hardy\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = \n| state       = \n| office      = Member-elect of the<br>[[U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[Nevada's 4th congressional district|Nevada's 4th district]]\n| term_start  = January 3, 2015\n| term_end    =\n| succeeding  = [[Steven Horsford]]\n| succeeded   =\n|state_house2=Nevada\n|district2=19th\n|term_start2=February 7, 2011\n|term_end2=\n|birth_name=\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1957|6|23}}\n|birth_place=[[St. George, Utah|St. George]], [[Utah]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n|party=[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]\n|spouse=Peri Jean\n|alma_mater=[[Dixie State College]]\n|children=4\n|religion=[[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] ([[Mormon]])\n|residence=[[Mesquite, Nevada|Mesquite]], [[Nevada]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n|website={{Official website|http://cresenthardyforcongress.com/}}\n}}\n'''Cresent Leo Hardy''' (born June 23, 1957) is an [[United States|American]] [[politician]] from the state of [[Nevada]]. A member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]], Hardy is a member of the [[Nevada State Assembly]], representing the 19th district.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationaljournal.com/article/535530|title=Nevada-4: Cresent Hardy (R)|work=www.nationaljournal.com|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHardy graduated from [[Virgin Valley High School]] and [[Dixie State College]]. He served as a [[city council]]or for [[Mesquite, Nevada|Mesquite]], [[Nevada]]. He was elected to the State Assembly in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2010/nov/03/gop-wins-rural-district-20-race-knocks-out-boulder/ |title=GOP wins rural District 20 race, knocks out Boulder City\xe2\x80\x99s Goya - Las Vegas Sun News |publisher=Lasvegassun.com |date=November 3, 2010 |accessdate=October 24, 2013}}</ref>\n\nHardy ran as a candidate for the [[United States House of Representatives]] in {{ushr|NV|4}}, held by [[Steven Horsford]] of the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]], in the [[United States House of Representatives elections in Nevada, 2014|2014 elections]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Call |first=Roll |url=http://www.rollcall.com/news/nevada_republicans_line_up_to_depose_reid_in_2016-228620-1.html |title=Nevada Republicans Line Up to Depose Reid in 2016 : Roll Call Politics |publisher=Rollcall.com |date=October 23, 2013 |accessdate=October 24, 2013}}</ref> Hardy defeated Horsford.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2014/nov/04/cresent-hardy-holds-surprising-lead-rep-steven-hor/|title=Cresent Hardy closes out surprising win over Rep. Steven Horsford|author=Amber Phillips|work=LasVegasSun.com|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://cresenthardyforcongress.com/}}\n* {{CongLinks|ballot=Cresent_Hardy|votesmart=121872|followthemoney=144939}}\n* {{Cite web|url=http://www.leg.state.nv.us/76th2011/Legislators/Assembly/Hardy.pdf|title=Legislative Biography \xe2\x80\x94 2011 Season|publisher=[[Nevada Legislature]]|format=pdf}}\n* {{Facebook|CresentHardyForCongress}}\n* {{Twitter|CresentHardy}}\n\n{{Nevada State Assembly}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hardy, Cresent}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dixie State University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Nevada Assembly]]\n[[Category:Nevada city council members]]\n[[Category:Nevada Republicans]]\n[[Category:People from Clark County, Nevada]]\n[[Category:People from St. George, Utah]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from Nevada]]\n[[Category:American Latter Day Saints]]\n\n{{Nevada-politician-stub}}"
